						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar used as foot-step in the Kallēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Bhillama—A.D. 1190.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged and worn out record is dated in the king's <hi rend="bold">regnal year 4, Sādhāraṇa, Kārtika śu. Pūrṇimā, Monday, Saṁkramaṇa,</hi> regularly corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1190, October 15, Monday.</hi> There was, however, no <hi rend="italic">saṁkramaṇa</hi> on that day.</p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to record a gift for the worship of god Svayaṁbhu Bijjalēśvara.</p>						

						</summary>
